      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2 Gradation 1, model form uncertainty need not be formally quantified; selection of constitutive models must be documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmarks for rotating blood-contacting devices. Power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) used with documented parameter sources. Model form assessment at Gradation 1 is acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2 Gradation 1, nominal values for all model inputs must be documented; formal uncertainty propagation is not required.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, pump geometry, boundary conditions) specified at nominal values with sources cited. Blood analog fluid properties taken from manufacturer datasheet. Formal input uncertainty propagation not required at this risk level."
    },
    {
